.TH POHODA-CLIENT-CHECKER 1 "" "1.0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pohoda\-client\-checker \- check Pohoda mServer connectivity
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pohoda-client-checker
[\fB\-e\fR \fIENV_FILE\fR] [\fB\-o\fR \fIOUTPUT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Connects to a Sormware Pohoda mServer instance and verifies connectivity,
authentication, and basic API health. Results are written to stdout or a
file specified with \fB\-o\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-environment =\fIFILE\fR
Path to the .env file containing connection parameters. Defaults to the
system environment.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output =\fIFILE\fR
Write result to \fIFILE\fR instead of stdout.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B POHODA_URL
Base URL of the Pohoda mServer instance.
.TP
.B POHODA_USERNAME
Username for mServer authentication.
.TP
.B POHODA_PASSWORD
Password for mServer authentication.
.TP
.B POHODA_ICO
Company ICO (tax identifier) to query.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pohoda-transaction-report (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>
